        "article_content_gLgQw8": {
          "type": "article_content",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Detoxing your home doesn’t have to mean binning everything at once. Start small. Think of it as a slow, thoughtful way to care for your space, just as you would for your body.</p><ul><li><strong>Choose multifunctional products.</strong> Look for all-purpose cleaners like Purdy & Figg’s Counter Clean to cut out clutter and single-use packaging.</li><li><strong>Check the label.</strong> Avoid parabens, phthalates, ammonia and synthetic dyes.</li><li><strong>Prioritise refills and reusables.</strong> A refillable glass bottle isn’t just better for the planet — it looks better on your shelf, too.</li><li><strong>Go seasonal.</strong> Like with food and skincare, switching up your scent with the seasons makes cleaning feel less like admin and more like self-care.</li></ul>",
            "content_class": "",
            "content_text-color": "#616161"
          }
        },
        "article_content_9fhJMj": {
          "type": "article_content",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p><em>And if you’re looking for a place to start? </em><em><strong>Purdy & Figg’s Seasonal Starter Kit</strong></em><em> includes a beautiful glass Bottle for Life, a high-performance microfibre cloth, and three natural scent refills, currently featuring the Limited Edition Calabrian Lemon. </em><em><strong>It’s £19.95 to get started, and it might just change how you feel about cleaning</strong></em><em>.</em></p>",
            "content_class": "content-last",
            "content_text-color": "#212121"
          }
        }
